# Trivy CVE allowlist — repo root.
#
# Trivy's `--ignorefile .trivyignore` auto-discovers this file when run
# from the repo root. One CVE id per line; `#` starts a comment.
#
# THE RULE: an entry here MUST be paired with a runtime mitigation
# (apt-get upgrade in the relevant Dockerfile, or a fix at the
# application layer). The .trivyignore is for "this CVE is known +
# tracked + mitigated in our build, but the BASE IMAGE TAG cannot be
# bumped because no rebuilt tag exists yet upstream". Without a
# runtime mitigation, do NOT add a CVE here.
#
# Every entry MUST include:
#   - the CVE id
#   - what it affects
#   - the fixed version (so an operator can confirm it's tracked)
#   - the mitigation we ship
#   - the trigger to remove the entry
#
# Audit cadence: review weekly. The CI gate's whole point is to fire
# loud on un-mitigated CVEs; a permanent ignore defeats it.

# =============================================================================
# Debian-bookworm CVEs in python:3.12-slim-bookworm
# Disclosed 2026-05-16. Upstream python image has not been rebuilt with
# the Debian security archive's patched packages yet (still on debian
# 12.13; fixes available in 12.13+u14 / +u3 / +u2 respectively).
# Runtime mitigation: infra/docker/dockerfiles/PythonWorker.Dockerfile
# now runs `apt-get upgrade -y --no-install-recommends` at build time,
# pulling the patched libc-bin / libcap2 / libsystemd0 / libudev1 from
# the Debian security archive. Our shipped image carries the fix;
# the trivy gate scans the upstream tag and cannot see the patch.
# REMOVE THIS BLOCK once the upstream python:3.12-slim-bookworm image
# is rebuilt (the trivy report will report 0 HIGH on its own; verify
# locally with `trivy image python:3.12-slim-bookworm`).
# =============================================================================

# glibc integer overflow in memalign → heap corruption.
# Affects: libc-bin, libc6. Fixed in 2.36-9+deb12u14.
CVE-2026-0861

# libcap: privilege escalation via TOCTOU race in cap_set_file().
# Affects: libcap2. Fixed in 1:2.66-4+deb12u3.
CVE-2026-4878

# systemd: arbitrary code execution / DoS via spurious IPC message.
# Affects: libsystemd0, libudev1. Fixed in 252.39-1~deb12u2.
CVE-2026-29111
